===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} ''[[spadu]]'', ''[[spada]]'', of Germanic origin. Cognate with Old Frisian ''[[spada]]'', Old Saxon ''[[spado]]'', German ''[[Spaten]]''. Ultimately from Proto-Indo-European ''*spə-dh-'', whence also Greek ''[[σπάθη]]'' (''spáthē'') ‘blade’, Hittite ''[[išpatar]]'' ‘spear’.

